# Borkeina

Borkeina is a React + Supabase web application that combines:

- matrimonial profile matching
- wedding products ecommerce
- wedding services marketplace
- separate admin console support

## Core Files

- `src/`
- `public/`
- `index.html`
- `package.json`
- `package-lock.json`
- `vite.config.js`
- `.env.example`
- `.gitignore`
- `vercel.json`
- `netlify.toml`

## Run Locally

```bash
npm install
npm run dev
```

## Build

```bash
npm run build
```

## Supabase Setup

Use this file in Supabase SQL Editor:

- [supabase-setup-nofunc.sql](C:/Users/rabin/Documents/Codex/2026-04-19-build-web-application-using-react-and/supabase-setup-nofunc.sql)

After signup, assign your admin user manually:

```sql
insert into public.user_roles (user_id, role)
values ('YOUR_AUTH_USER_ID', 'admin');
```

## Deployment

- Public domain: `www.borkeina.com`
- Admin domain: `admin.borkeina.com`

Environment variables:

```env
VITE_PUBLIC_HOST=www.borkeina.com
VITE_PUBLIC_URL=https://www.borkeina.com
VITE_ADMIN_HOST=admin.borkeina.com
VITE_ADMIN_URL=https://admin.borkeina.com
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://xboeoxwcqihziasxntee.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
```
